title: The Hobbit
description: A fantasy novel by J.R.R. Tolkien about a hobbit's journey to recover a treasure guarded by a dragon.

title: Anna Karenina
description: A novel by Leo Tolstoy about a woman's tragic love affair, set against the backdrop of Russian society.

title: Great Expectations
description: A novel by Charles Dickens, following the life of Pip, an orphan who rises through society through an unexpected benefactor.

title: The Brothers Karamazov
description: A philosophical novel by Fyodor Dostoevsky about the moral dilemmas of three brothers and their relationship with their father.

title: The Lord of the Rings
description: An epic fantasy trilogy by J.R.R. Tolkien, telling the story of the journey to destroy a powerful ring and defeat the Dark Lord Sauron.

title: Jane Eyre
description: A novel by Charlotte Brontë, following the life of an orphaned girl who becomes a governess and falls in love with her employer, Mr. Rochester.

title: Don Quixote
description: A novel by Miguel de Cervantes about an elderly man who, inspired by chivalric literature, sets off on an adventure as a knight-errant.

title: Les Misérables
description: A historical novel by Victor Hugo, set in post-revolutionary France, following the lives of several characters, particularly Jean Valjean.

title: The Divine Comedy
description: An epic poem by Dante Alighieri, describing the journey of the soul through Hell, Purgatory, and Heaven.

title: Catch-22
description: A satirical novel by Joseph Heller about the absurdities and contradictions of war, following a group of World War II bombers.
